Slovenia, officially the Republic of Slovenia, is a nation state in southern Central Europe, located at the crossroads of main European cultural and trade routes. The capital and largest city is Ljubljana. {{W|Slovenia}} In 2014, Ljubljana won the European Green Capital Award for 2016 for its environmental achievements. {{W|Ljubljana#Parks and other green spaces}}

